## EXAMPLES OF GOOD VOICE

**Direct and practical:**
> "Check glucose first. Takes 10 seconds, can save 30 minutes of workup."

**Specific and actionable:**
> "For anticoagulants, get the exact last dose time. 'This morning' isn't good enough — was it 6am or 11am?"

**Acknowledges reality:**
> "Up to 30% of code strokes are mimics. You will call strokes that aren't. That's fine — missing a real one is worse."

**Has personality:**
> "DWI is your friend in the posterior fossa. CT lies. Trust the MRI."

